{
  "noisy_sentences": "<noisy_sentences>The sentences about the new coffee shop, the artisanal donuts, and the stray numbers (521, 887 discover) are irrelevant.</noisy_sentences>",
  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Find the largest whole number less than 2012 all of whose divisors have at most two 1's in their binary representations.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "Step 1. Note that for any whole number n that satisfies the condition, n itself (as a divisor) must have at most two 1’s in its binary representation. The numbers whose binary representations have at most two 1’s are exactly the powers of 2 (one 1) and the sums of two distinct powers of 2 (exactly two 1’s). \nStep 2. Since n < 2012, n must be either 2^a or 2^a + 2^b with a > b and n < 2012. A power of 2 maximum here is 2^10 = 1024 because 2^11 = 2048 is too large. \nStep 3. Check the possibility with two ones: For numbers of the form 2^a + 2^b, we want to maximize n. The best possibility is to choose the highest exponents possible while keeping the sum under 2012. With a = 10 (since 2^10 = 1024 is the largest power of 2 below 2012) and b = 9 (next highest power, 2^9 = 512), we get n = 2^10 + 2^9 = 1024 + 512 = 1536. \nStep 4. Verify that 1536 meets the condition. Any divisor d of 1536 must also be of the form 2^k or a product 2^k times an odd factor that divides (2^(10-9) + 1). Here, note that 1536 factors as 2^9 × 3 (since 2^10+2^9 = 2^9*(2+1) = 2^9*3). The divisors of 1536 are all numbers of the form 2^r or 2^r × 3 (with r from 0 to 9). In binary, any power of 2 is of the form 1 followed by zeros (one 1), and any number of the form 2^r × 3 equals 3×2^r which in binary is simply the binary representation of 3 (11) shifted left by r places (so it contains exactly two 1’s). Thus every divisor of 1536 has at most two 1’s in its binary representation. \nStep 5. Confirm no larger candidate exists below 2012 because the only other candidate using two ones with a > 10 would force 2^a to be greater than 2012. \nTherefore, 1536 is indeed the largest whole number less than 2012 that satisfies the condition.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>1536</answer>"
}

