  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>679 contestants participated in HMMT February 2017. Let N be the number of these contestants who performed at or above the median score in at least one of the three individual tests. Estimate N.</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "Step 1: For any individual test, the median splits the contestants into two equal halves. Thus, for each test, half of the contestants score at or above the median. \nStep 2: A contestant fails to score at or above the median in a particular test with probability 1/2. Assuming the three tests are independent in this context, the probability that a given contestant scores below the median in all three tests is (1/2)^3 = 1/8. \nStep 3: Therefore, the probability that a contestant scores at or above the median in at least one of the three tests is 1 - 1/8 = 7/8. \nStep 4: Multiplying this probability by the total number of contestants gives an estimate for N: N ≈ 679 × (7/8) = (679 × 7) / 8 = 4753 / 8 ≈ 594.125. \nStep 5: Rounding to the nearest whole number, we estimate N ≈ 594.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>594</answer>"
}

{
